{
  "texts": [
    "Experience, Gender, or Age Categorization publications tended to use a wide range of feature types but were the most frequent users of scanpath and AOIbased features, which are mostly due to using scanpath comparison metrics, where they compare pairs of scanpaths and use the scores as inputs to the ML algorithm.",
    "When considering traditional ML and neural networks, we found that traditional ML publications used all feature types.",
    "Almost all of the features, i.e., 118 out of 126 features, were for traditional ML algorithms.",
    "However, neural networks focused on a less diverse set of features, i.e., 46 out of 126 features.",
    "After the general insights toward the different features, we wanted to highlight three feature groups."
  ]
}